#: ../../user/advanced-topics/resize-disk-image.rst:102
#: b5cd4e80ec8e4eb7b0593d0f63ddd808
msgid ""
"Qubes will automatically grow the filesystem for you on all app qubes "
"with Qubes packages installed (which are all app qubes installed from "
"templates, cloned from templates etc. - if you have not created an empty "
"HVM and installed a Linux distribution in it, without using Qubes "
"repositories, you are almost certainly safe). Otherwise, you will see "
"that there is unallocated free space at the end of your primary disk. You"
" can use standard linux tools like ``fdisk`` and ``resize2fs`` to make "
"this space available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/resize-disk-image.rst:105
#: 58ed1028d22242d5acbbf59836e43ddc
msgid "Decreasing the size of Disk Images"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/advanced-topics/resize-disk-image.rst:108
#: 3a367020648347d191e12a56fac44fb2
msgid ""
"The number shown for “storage max size” does not mean that the storage is"
" really using that amount. In most cases you need not worry about the "
"size shown. If you have increased the max size, and do not need it, then "
"you *can* reduce the allocated size, but there is a risk of data loss. "
"Remember you really dont need to do this."
msgstr ""

